\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs26\b 1. Suite and Architecture\b0\fs22\par
\par
Arcade Commander 2.0 is a 3-component Windows suite:\par
\par
- `ArcadeCommanderV2.exe`: operator UI and workflow host.\par
- `ACLighter.exe`: local runtime lighting service/tray app.\par
- `ACDispatch.exe`: command/event dispatcher used by scripts and frontend hooks.\par
\par
All components share runtime data under `data/` and communicate locally over loopback networking.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 1.1 Component Responsibilities\b0\par
\par
`ArcadeCommanderV2.exe`:\par
\par
- User-facing control plane.\par
- Owns Commander, Emulator, Game Manager, FX Editor, and Controller Config tabs.\par
- Loads and saves profiles, game records, and shared FX/animation libraries.\par
\par
`ACLighter.exe`:\par
\par
- Runtime apply engine for live lighting behavior.\par
- Exposes local listener endpoint used by Commander and Dispatch.\par
- Provides tray-level stress/test/reset actions.\par
\par
`ACDispatch.exe`:\par
\par
- External trigger path for game events and automation.\par
- Supports idle reset, event signaling, animation forcing, and ROM-driven mapping loads.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 1.2 Runtime Communication Model\b0\par
\par
Default local endpoint:\par
\par
- Host: `127.0.0.1`\par
- Port: `6006`\par
\par
Expected flow:\par
\par
1. Operator configures behavior in Commander UI.\par
2. UI writes/reads runtime JSON data under `data/`.\par
3. UI and ACDispatch send runtime packets to ACLighter.\par
4. ACLighter applies effect and animation output to configured hardware path.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 1.3 Shared Catalog Model\b0\par
\par
Effects and animations are designed as shared catalogs.\par
A saved entry in FX Editor should be available from Commander and Emulator selectors.\par
\par
Shared files:\par
\par
- Effects: `data/library/AC_FXLibrary.json`\par
- Animations: `data/library/AC_AnimationLibrary.json`\par
