\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs26\b 11. Troubleshooting Guide\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 11.1 No Lighting Response\b0\par
\par
Symptoms:\par
\par
- No visible LED output after apply or tests.\par
\par
Likely causes:\par
\par
- ACLighter not running.\par
- Port/path mismatch.\par
- Hardware path disconnected.\par
\par
Actions:\par
\par
1. Confirm ACLighter tray icon exists.\par
2. Verify listener path and selected port.\par
3. Run `ALL OFF` then `APPLY`.\par
4. Run `LED TEST` and `BTN TEST`.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 11.2 Effect Exists in FX Editor but Missing Elsewhere\b0\par
\par
Symptoms:\par
\par
- Effect appears in FX Editor but not Commander/Emulator selectors.\par
\par
Likely causes:\par
\par
- Save did not persist to shared library.\par
- Selector cache not refreshed.\par
- Entry format inconsistent.\par
\par
Actions:\par
\par
1. Verify entry exists in `data/library/AC_FXLibrary.json` or animation file.\par
2. Reload selectors or restart app.\par
3. Re-save using shared library path.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\b 11.3 Preview Works but Hardware Does Not\b0\par
\par
Symptoms:\par
\par
- Emulator/preview updates but cabinet LEDs do not.\par
\par
Likely causes:\par
\par
- ACLighter listener path unavailable.\par
- Hardware transport failure.\par
- Port selection mismatch.\par
\par
Actions:\par
\par
1. Confirm ACLighter active state.\par
2. Validate physical connections.\par
3. Run hardware-side diagnostics via `LED TEST`.\par
\par
